metadata.name: Happy Accidents #162
metadata.description:
Sometimes when you're working on your Creative Coding project, you make a change to the code and it breaks. But maybe that's a good thing. This project was created as a fun expression of what can happen if you allow yourself to go down the rabbit hole, and further break your code until you come up with a new idea.

Special thanks to @clayheaton and @sableRaph for the coding tips and tricks.

metadata.name: How Stars Really Look #74
metadata.description:
When I was a kid, I used to draw stars as circles, while my friends drew them as 5-pointed "regular" stars. I used to think they were wrong.

But when I grew up and saw a real star very closely, I realized that it was I who was wrong.

In "How Stars Really Look", I present to you a hundred images of real stars, which are billions of lightyears away from us, and which cannot be seen by eyes or by any device.

* * *

This is my 1st "Thank You" project to show my gratitude to the fxhash community for supporting me and collecting my previous generative art projects. THANK YOU!! üíú

Press S to save as PNG.

Made by: yenren / twitter.com/yenrenART
Made with: JavaScript + HTML Canvas
License: LICENSE.txt

metadata.name: Zometric #40
metadata.description:
A journey into geometric shapes.
Real art is not hidden behind complicated and obscure forms. In this collection, we have tried to achieve a unique visual clarity by using the basic visual elements. A pure mixture between piet mondrian and paul klee. A combination of visual language of classical and modern art movements. Over 15 000 combination can be generated.
Made in p5.js

metadata.name: Ideocartography: Animal God Sigils #56
metadata.description:
This piece explores some ideocartgography created with p5.js. Everything is rendered in 3D and captured from a moving camera viewpoint, without clearing the screen. Boxes and ellipsoids of different sizes and colors are recursively shrunk, and their overlapping edges and surfaces draw the resulting shapes you see. The mind does the rest.

5% of splits go to the processing foundation
25% of royalties go to the primary minter (thank you for collecting!)

metadata.name: Fluxus | Collab with Rose Jackson #15
metadata.description:
Generative art piece created with code in Hydra (hydra.ojack.xyz) and in collaboration with artist Rose Jackson @in_cloudlands

This generative art piece is inspired by Rose's textile work and the physical phenomena associated with fluid mechanics. Space is not a mere concept: it is an experienced reality where frames, forces and flows interact in a creative dynamic. From this base, we have related texture, movement and color in a piece of dynamic flows like our lives.

Hydra is a toolkit for live coding of network visuals created by Olivia Jack (ojack.xyz)

Collab by Rose Jackson & Daniel Oropeza
Panama City, Panama
17/03/2022

metadata.name: Capture Bigfoot - Wild Paper Series #202
metadata.description:
In the wilderness of the Pacific Northwest, a legendary creature hides.  Some have tried to find proof of its existence, but have failed.  Will you be the one to capture evidence of the elusive Bigfoot?  

This generative work features hand-drawn ink sketches that have been digitally enhanced, and assembled into these beautiful vistas of distant mountains, mid-range foothills, stands on conifers, large boulders, . . . and, of course, the elusive Bigfoot.

Draw the super-rare Squatch Card for an extra bonus!

Functions: 
Press SPACE to download and save image as a png.
Click or tap the canvas to toggle full screen.

Squatch Card Special Function:
Press 'V' to view assets layout card.
Refresh token to toggle back to landscape.
